
                       List of maintainers and how to submit changes

Please try to follow the guidelines below. This will make things easier on
the maintainers. Not all of these guidelines matter for every trivial patch,
so apply some common sense.

    1. Always describe what your patch does and why.
    2. Prefer smaller, focused patches over large omnibus changes.
    3. Add a test alongside every non-trivial change.
    4. Match the coding style described in Documentation/coding-style.md.
    5. Sign off your commits (Signed-off-by:) if the change is non-trivial.
    6. Route each patch to the maintainer(s) of the affected subsystem
       (grep -w SUBSYSTEM MAINTAINERS to find them).

Descriptions of section entries:

    M: Maintainer's Full Name <address@domain>
    R: Designated Reviewer <address@domain>
    F: Files and directories wildcard patterns.
    W: Web-page with status/info
    T: SCM tree type and location.
    S: Status, one of the following:
         Supported    - Someone is paid to look after this.
         Maintained   - Someone actively looks after this.
         Odd Fixes    - Only very obvious fixes accepted.
         Orphan       - No current maintainer, submissions welcome.

